21 SECTION 4. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
22 General Assembly of the State of Arkansas that amendments to the Arkansas
23 Constitution impact the public peace, health, and safety of each citizen of
24 this state; that to protect the public peace, health, and safety of the
25 citizens of this state, it is necessary to increase the threshold for passage
26 of a constitutional amendment proposed under Arkansas Constitution, Article
27 5, § 1, to ensure that constitutional amendments are supported by an
28 appropriate number of voters to justify an amendment to the Arkansas
29 Constitution; and that this act should become effective at the earliest
30 opportunity to ensure that its provisions are in place for the 2026 general
31 election. Therefore, an emergency is declared to exist, and this act being
32 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health, and
33 safety shall become effective on:
